The paper focuses on user studies related to password management, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). It also discusses the use of mnemonic techniques and spaced repetition, which are relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cryptography (cs.IT). The study involves remote participants, which could fall under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
